Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "firma" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations:

1. Moja *firma* se bavi prodajom elektronskih uređaja. (My *company* deals with the sale of electronic devices.)
2. Imamo problema s finansiranjem naše *firme*. (We have problems with financing our *company*.)
3. Ulica u kojoj se nalazi naša *firma* nosi ime po poznatom srpskom naučniku. (The street where our *company* is located is named after a famous Serbian scientist.)
4. *Firma* u kojoj radim organizuje team building aktivnosti za zaposlene. (*The company* I work for organizes team building activities for employees.)
5. Ovaj dokument je potrebno potpisati i overiti kod nadležnog organa i poslati *firmi*. (This document needs to be signed and certified by the competent authority and sent to the *company*.)
6. Kako bismo izbjegli kašnjenje, trebamo uplatiti avans *firmi*. (In order to avoid delay, we need to pay an advance to the *company*.)
7. Posao u toj *firmi* ima odlične beneficije, ali je konkurencija jaka. (The job in that *company* has excellent benefits, but the competition is strong.)
8. Nova *firma* u gradu nudi inovativne proizvode i usluge. (The new *company* in town offers innovative products and services.)
9. Čujem da je tvoja *firma* postigla sjajne poslovne rezultate prošle godine. (I hear that your *company* achieved great business results last year.)
10. Moramo osigurati da se *firma* pridržava propisa i standarda u svom poslovanju. (We need to ensure that the *company* adheres to regulations and standards in its operations.)